2009-10-12 Vasile Jureschi  vjuresch@sohia.inria.fr, vasile.jureschi@gmail.com
	* added namespace "paagent" to prevent name clashes (e.g. Event class)
	 
	* fixed the cpulimiting, as it was not implemented for every action 
		- modified Runner class 
	
	* modified the starter classes (Runner, Controller, NodeStarter 
	  and derived classes) to use a simpler way of passing arguments. 
	  In the paagent_server the configuration options are now
	  passed around using a Configuration singleton class. 
	
	* added handling for the <jvm_args> option in the configuration xml
	    - modified the Configuration class and NodeStarter class
	    
2009-10-12 Vasile Jureschi  vjuresch@sohia.inria.fr, vasile.jureschi@gmail.com
	
	* added string GetJVMParamsString() const; in Configuration class to get 
	the string of parameters

2009-10-12 Vasile Jureschi  vjuresch@sohia.inria.fr, vasile.jureschi@gmail.com

   * added arguments parsing in CustomNodeStarter constructor by appending the 
     extra arguments to the exec_arguments vector

2009-10-13 Vasile Jureschi  vjuresch@sohia.inria.fr, vasile.jureschi@gmail.com

   * added <jvm_memory> tag handling in NodeStarter::Initialize by adding it to
     the exec_arguments vector
   * changed this->jvm_params.empty()  to this->jvm_params.clear() in 
     Configuration::SetJVMParams, added the empty() instead of clear() by 
     mistake
   * added <use_all_cpus> handling in NodeStarter::Initialize by adding
     -native or -green to the JVM parameters
   * added <processPriority> handling in Watcher class through the renice method
     The named constructors were refactored to accept a pointer to and event and 
     an action. This was less cumbersome than passing a long list of arguments.  

